A total of 456 respiratory specimens were tested: 161 respiratory samples from (102 individuals) hematology/oncology patients in the immunocompromised group, and 295 samples (from 295 individuals) in the control group. Results were reported as copies per cell and copies per mL. These methods of normalization were highly correlated, with an R
2 of 0.87 (Fig. 1
).
